# 💊 Pharma Data Engineering Platform using Microsoft Fabric

An end-to-end Data Engineering project built using Microsoft Fabric to demonstrate enterprise-style data ingestion, transformation, analytics, and reporting for the pharmaceutical domain.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project simulates a real-world pharmaceutical analytics platform where data from multiple sources is ingested, transformed, and analyzed using Microsoft Fabric.

The solution follows the Medallion Architecture (Bronze, Silver, Gold) to ensure scalable, reliable, and high-quality data processing.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Build an end-to-end data engineering solution using Microsoft Fabric.
- Implement Medallion Architecture.
- Perform data cleaning and transformation using Spark Notebooks.
- Store curated data for reporting.
- Create interactive Power BI dashboards.
- Maintain project source code using Git Integration.

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| Microsoft Fabric | Unified Analytics Platform |
| OneLake | Data Storage |
| Lakehouse | Raw & Curated Storage |
| Data Pipelines | Data Ingestion |
| Spark Notebooks | Data Transformation |
| SQL Warehouse | Analytics |
| Power BI | Dashboard & Visualization |
| GitHub | Version Control |

---

## 🏗 Architecture

```
Source Systems
      │
      ▼
Data Pipeline
      │
      ▼
Bronze Layer
      │
      ▼
Silver Layer
      │
      ▼
Gold Layer
      │
      ▼
Warehouse
      │
      ▼
Power BI Dashboard
```

---

## 📂 Project Workflow

### Data Ingestion

- Ingest pharmaceutical datasets into OneLake
- Store raw data in Bronze Layer

### Data Transformation

- Data cleansing
- Remove duplicates
- Handle null values
- Data type conversion
- Business rule implementation

### Data Modeling

Create analytical tables for reporting.

### Reporting

Power BI dashboards provide KPIs such as

- Total Sales
- Revenue
- Orders
- Product Performance
- Regional Analysis
- Monthly Trends

